The paper proposes a method for inferring refinement types of higher-order functional programs, which falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL). The method involves optimization of refinement types, which can be seen as a constraint optimization problem, and the use of invariant generation, which are topics in logic and verification (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions safety and termination properties, which are topics in formal methods (cs.FL). Finally, the paper discusses non-determinism in programs, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
